<headline>Rip Current Statement issued April 10 at 3:18PM CDT until April 11 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH MONDAY EVENING...
* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents expected.
* WHERE...Brazoria Islands, Matagorda Islands, Bolivar Peninsula
and Galveston Island Counties.
* WHEN...Through Monday evening.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.</description>
<instruction>Swim near a lifeguard and away from rocks, jetties and piers.
If caught in a rip current, relax and float. Don`t swim against
the current. If able, swim in a direction following the shoreline.
If unable to escape, face the shore and call or wave for help.</instruction>
